items.name: Tatra 87 (1937-1950) V8
items.description:
Choose SDXL or SD 1.5 version from the menu on the top.

The Tatra 87 (T87) is a car crafted by the Czechoslovak manufacturer Tatra between 1936 and 1950. It stands as one of the fastest production cars of its time. It served as a predecessor to the VW Beetle in terms of its design concept, as the technical documentation was stolen by the occupying forces in 1939. Furthermore, it heavily inspired Porsche's design. Production of the T87 continued after World War II, and it gained fame through a world-traveling round trip undertaken by Hanzelka and Zikmund from 1947 to 1950. Notable owners of this car include John Steinbeck, Ernst Heinkel, Erwin Rommel, and Jay Leno.

SDXL 1024x1024, default weight 1 should work, use lower or higher value to create fictional vintage cars.

SD 1.5 768x768 (but various ratios and resolutions will do). Experiment with weights 0.15-0.8, CLIP SKIP 1-2. The model does not need a specific token (car with a description is enough). Add characters with Regional Prompter and/or ControlNet (faces need to be usually repaired with an inpaint, unless they are close to the camera).

Rate the Lora, it helps... Constructive comments are very welcome, this is an ongoing project.

For tutorials and guides on generative AI applications in art, graphic design, 3D and AR/VR, check my website sandner.art in section https://sandner.art/articles/ai/

items.name: WW1 - Renault FT Tank
items.description:
The famous Renault FT (also known as FT17) used by the French army during World War 1 is the first tank in history to have a mobile turret, a design still used today.

How to use

Weighted around 1 for best results but will vary according to the checkpoint and other settings. You can go as low as 0.5 (it will look more like a generic tank) or you can go high like 1.5 for experimental results.

Trained on SD 1.5 base. Tested on all top 20 checkpoints. Epoch 7 on a total of 10, 23 images from real tanks and toy tanks, some with background, some without background. With multiple colours and camouflage, you can try playing with it. Same thing for insignia, serial numbers, and symbols painted on the armour.

The double cannon will not always work, it's tricky to get a 100% success rate on such a small part. But it should be good enough, especially since it's a small cannon it gets it right most of the time.

items.name: Drive-Thru Window Operator (LORA)
items.description:
"Hello there, Civitai, can I take your order?"

I basically just thought of a random, unique idea of having someone as a drive-thru window operator and lo and behold, here it is. That, and when I do the prompts of someone being inside a drive-thru window, SD usually generates random locations inside the restaurant for my subjects, so I wanted to refine that. Let the hilarity ensue!

Recommended settings:

Make sure you check the hires fix (without it, the LoRA could produce very blurry results, especially with the faces)

Upscale by 2, to either 768x768 or 1024x1024 (for best quality)

Sampler: Euler a or DPM++ 2M Karras (they're the best samplers that I've used for the model since others aren't as satisfactory with it, imo)

Denoising: ~0.55-0.75

CFG scale: ~6-8

LoRA weight: ~0.6-0.9

Checkpoints: Realistic Vision, Deliberate, Dreamshaper, and Lyriel are my personal recommendations since they're the most accurate when it comes to depictions of people.

Make sure you add the keyword "inside the drive-thru window" in order for your subject to actually be inside the window. You can also add keywords of "headset", "apron", "cap hat", and "holding out (insert food here)" to make your image more creative.

Negative prompt that works well:

deformed, bad anatomy, disfigured, poorly drawn face, mutation, mutated, extra limb, ugly, disgusting, poorly drawn hands, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, malformed hands, blurry, ((mutated hands and fingers)), duplicate images, duplicate, (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, (mutated hands and fingers:1.4), disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, blurry, amputation, EasyNegative, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t

DeepNegative and EasyNegative are very recommended.

Suggestions and feedback are welcome! I hope you enjoy!

As of 2023, Sara Bell is still active in the adult film industry, and her fan base continues to grow. Her social media presence includes Twitter, where she goes by the handle @Sara_Bell_XX69.

💡Workflow Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75 - 1.2.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.😈

    • Tile pre-sample and model is good for extreme close ups

    • I use segmentation for lots of my generations now.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Try the Ultimate SD upscale script!

  • Sometimes I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

items.name: Uncanny
items.description:
In my unwavering pursuit to refine and explore new horizons, I've developed a new model which I'm excited to unveil in two distinct versions!

Highcontrast - this is finetuned based on general purpose model with fixed noise schedule! Inspired by this reddit post. Beware, this model has a tendency towards rendering very dark images. So, when drafting your prompts, keep the lighting in mind. It might just be the only model capable to produce images with a white background!

General - this is model designed for imitating photos. has been tailored to mimic the aesthetics of photography. This might be your cup of tea, or it might not be - there are various photorealistic models out there, but I believe this one delivers outstanding results. Especially when you apply loras <lora:add_detail:1>, <lora:FilmG2:0.8>. Model is merge from my private finetunes.

By supporting me on Ko-fi (https://ko-fi.com/michelangelofussion), you're not only empowering me to maintain and improve the current model, but also enabling me to expand my research and train even more advanced models

Enjoy the exploration!

My other model:
StyleJourney - model finetuned on MJ images

items.name: Three sister
items.description:
训练与文本编辑条件：

三人次数不同，图片数量不同。

二姐和三妹次数相同，服装三妹变化大。

尽量排除三人趋同，老二描述特征减少。

老大反推详细内容，固定头像，

老二固定风格:汉服，

老三固定头像、半身像、全身像。

本来想做三人LORA，结果参数很好LOSS=0.1,然而是个失败品，所以单生成了一个低学习率的（loss=0.078）大姐，意外好用。

第二版大姐远景还是不尽如人意，相反新生成二姐V2最好版叙述为：erjie,three sister,hanfu,没想到意外成功，基本上可以明确的是图像中央渲染最大的图形就是固定目标，文字只是辅助，太多图和文字只会造成训练的低学习率，给图AI明白你要做什么，训练时背景最好是白色或单色调。

原图是664X1080，推荐生成图大小640X768会有不错效果。

畸形的情况可以调整CFG=4,或等待后续LORA发布，新的模型会添加各种角度图片，以及提高出图稳定性。

I originally intended to do a three person LORA, but the parameter was very good, and the loss=0.1. However, it was a failure product, so I generated a low learning rate (loss=0.78) elder sister(dajie), which unexpectedly worked well. I will upload the LORA for my two younger sisters tomorrow and the day after.

The original image is 664X1080, and it is recommended to generate an image size of 640X768will have a good effect.

The abnormal situation can be adjusted to CFG=4, or waiting for subsequent LORA release. The new model will add various angle images and improve the stability of the image

items.name: Masters of the Universe - Teela
items.description:
BY THE POWER OF GRAYSKULL

I noticed a distinct lack of 80's characters on here and being a Gen-X'er, I had to rectify that issue. To continue the series, I now present the OG Muscle Mommy Teela, Captain of the Guard from Masters of the Universe. This Lora was trained on images from the 1980's Funimation cartoon and product images for the WETA/Sideshow maquette as well as the 80's era toys. I did not use images from the live-action movie nor the new Netflix series.

Image was trained on SD1.5, so it is good for most other checkpoints. I would recommend setting the strength to 0.8-1. Highres.fx = VERY YES. I usually go about 1/2 of my initial steps with a denoising strength of 0.3-0.4. To get the most out of this LoRA, I strongly recommend using fitCorder's very excellent FitCorderMix v1.6 - Verstatile

Activation word is "80s_Teela". To get the classic look, use "red hair" and "blue eyes". While muscle tone is built in, specifying "arm muscles" and "thigh muscles" can get you that real warrior look.

Good luck, have fun, and stay tuned for more 80's icons!

Generate using a weight of 0.4-1 like this: <lora:standingFootjobv119:1>


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.name: Ikigai 2.5D
items.description:
Does what you want. Does what you love. Does what you're good at! (except hands)
Your Ikigai!


I made this mix because I really love fine details provided by some models, but didn't want be bound to a certain look for faces, lighting, etc.

This model focuses mainly on 2.5D and semi-realism, and handles loras, TIs, long/short prompts, and everything in between very well!


V2:

Now with even better lighting, more detail, and no loras needed to achieve the look!! This iteration plays a lot nicer with Textual Inversions without the need of realism, detail, or artist loras, but they're still welcome!

Added the following models to the mix

WWColor
Real Moon

V1:

My usual settings:
Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras
Sample Steps: 20-35
Upscaler: ESRGAN_4x
Deniose: 0.5
CFG: 5-9

Model has no VAE baked in, I personally use Graprfruit-VAE

By no means is this law, feel free to experiment and I'd love to see your results!!

For inpainting, I generally limit to Only Masked to 800 x 800 or lower and 0.5 denoise, as it will start to get a little too detailed otherwise. You shouldn't need to change your prompt at all when inpainting faces to get a good result. This was a goal of mine, as I prefer not to have to do any extra steps in my workflow if possible.

This mix comprises of:
MajicMix Lux
MIX-Pro-V4
Babes 2.0

For the semi-realism look in a couple of the example images, I HIGHLY recommend the lora below at a weight of 0.1-0.2:
Danni-2D (looks to be removed, but any lora that would add realism to models like AOM3)

Model also plays reaaaally well with 2D artist style loras like DevilHS, Gopher, SamDoesArt, etc. and will often help with the hands issue.

All example images have no post-work beyond inpainting and SD upscale within the webUI.
